5:
Pardon me for intruding.
It's unusual for you to call on me
while I'm at the academy, father.
8:
There's someone I wanted to
introduce to you.
...Kamir.
10:
H-hello. My name is Kamir Rahl. It's...
an honor to finally make your
acquaintance.
13:
Rahl. That name sounds familiar...
That wouldn't be THE House Rahl,
whose business has been booming
of late?
16:
Is this man intended to be my
suitor? How many times is that now,
Father?
19:
Six. If you'd just do a better job of
concealing that fiery temper of
yours, I wouldn't have had to go that
far.
22:
Surely you can't expect me to marry
a man who is my lesser? They
wouldn't be able to become
president and lead our company.
25:
Enough of that already. You're a
brilliant girl, yes... but you don't have
what it takes to be at the top.
26:
Look at you, still content with playing
second fiddle in that silly club of
yours! I only allow you to continue
that out of the goodness of my
heart.
32:
It's clear to me you don't even want
to reach the top. Quit the club and
come home after school—Karim
and I will try to make something
worthwhile out of you.
35:
Unfortunately, I can't comply with
your wishes. For one, it's too early to
just quit now.
38:
You were the one who told me to try
to be the best, were you not? Well, I
laid out a plan, and I'm going to
stick to it.
42:
Just you wait—you'll get what's
coming to you soon, Father. I'll show
you some real results and finally
shut you up.
47:
I'm so sorry for having you carry all
those instruments, Nimbus!
51:
Don't sweat it. I had nothing else to
do anyway.
53:
But what's the deal with all the new
instruments? Why are you swapping
them out?
57:
Something's come up that requires
us to pull out all the stops! Hence,
new instruments!
65:
We're aiming for the TOP here. Do
you think we can win the Palpebran
International Music Festival with you
DRAGGING like that?!
68:
With such mediocre playing, we
won't even make it past the
QUALIFIERS, for crying out loud!
74:
Would that "something" have to do
with those guys and their psycho-
conductor?
78:
She told me that—at this rate—she'd
have to quit the marching band.
Actually, the same thing happened
once before too.
81:
Neither of us wants that to happen,
so we're going to try to show her
family that we're producing some
results.
87:
Hehe. I think it's just about time for a
break, don't you think?
93:
Hmm?! Just what do you think
you're doing?!
96:
We have to go all out, of course,
but... Elsie, do you remember our
motto?
100:
I'm sorry. I need to go cool my head
for a while.
105:
Nimbus, would you go and talk to
her for me? I think you're the right
person for the job.
111:
Well, aren't you full of energy.
Thought you were "cooling your
head"?
115:
There's no time to rest. Student
bands don't usually get to
participate in events this important,
you know.
118:
I've brought the band here for my
own selfish reasons. Needless to say,
I have to do my absolute best.
122:
You've brought them here, huh. I see.
Guess that's why she wanted me to
do this.
125:
You know, maybe your bandmates
just ain't got what it takes?
131:
What do you mean you're going to
quit, Elsie?
136:
You're the Drum Major. I'm not. I can't
reach the top, so there's no point in
me sticking around—
140:
But that's not true! Chasing the top
spot itself can be fun—you said that
yourself, Elsie!
144:
That's how I got here. I followed your
advice and enjoyed my journey!
156:
Ha... Hahaha... Hohohoho!
Don't make me laugh like that,
Nimbus! You underestimate them.
161:
...Or maybe I'm the one who has
been underestimating them. They're
eager to do their best, and are
willing to put up with me—and I with
them.
167:
I'm grateful for your help, Nimbus.
Thanks to you, I've realized how to
set the perfect trap for my no-good
father.
171:
I'd forgotten the fundamental
impulse that underlies this whole
endeavor.
174:
Being at the top is a means to an
end; the end being enriching
oneself. If one is enriched by other
means, such as "having fun," then so
be it.
177:
However, what we businesspeople
are after isn't spiritual enrichment,
but the monetary kind. We need
tangible results. What will my results
be this time, then...
181:
Oh, Eloise! Thanks so much for
helping out before!
184:
Thanks to you, our special feature
was a huge hit! Sponsors are lining
up to work with us now!
187:
Special feature? Sponsors? What is
all this about? What are you
planning?
190:
I'm trying to make my club activities
into a lucrative venture for Father,
that's what.
193:
I had the Oculus write a piece about
our activities. It's quite popular
among the general public, it seems.
195:
People all over the city know of our
marching band. Sponsors would be
eager to have their brand
associated with us.
197:
And what if they found out that at
the center of said marching band is
none other than the heiress to
Magento Co.?
200:
A-are you really sure you can flaunt
the company name like that in
public? Aren't you afraid of the
repercussions?
203:
No. The company will be mine one
day anyway. I won't hear any
whining!
207:
I definitely won't be hearing any
from you, will I, Kamir? House Rahl
will cooperate with us, I assume?
212:
It's okay. You'll get used to her way
of doing things soon enough.
218:
This is all just insurance, of course.
Just in case. Our performance will
be what really makes father shut his
mouth.
221:
Preliminaries will be a breeze. We'll
get through them, no matter what!
Hohohoho!
